    "All training runs were run on 2 H100 nodes (16 GPUs) unless otherwise stated.",
    "For rubric and citation scoring, we use GPT-4.1-mini (gpt-4.1-mini-2025-04-14) as an LM judge; we use GPT-4.1 as an rubric generator for both initial and evolving rubrics.",
    "For our final training run, we ran for 25 days, using roughly 9700 GPU hours to take 1900 training steps, or 6.8 epochs over our training data.",
    "We note that the RL run did not seem to saturate even with this long training time, and we may release future checkpoints with improved performance.",
    "We found increasing compute did not improve RL training speed, due to being limited by API rate-limits during rollouts."
